Thick Driver :-
If Driver require some extra component to communicate with DataBase then that driver is called as Thick Driver.

Example :- Type1,2,3 are thick driver as they need ODBC Driver, Vendor Specific Native Libraries and MiddleWare Server to communicate with DataBase.

Thin Driver :-
If Driver require no extra component to communicate with DataBase then that driver is called as Thin Driver.

Example :- Type 4 Driver that directly communicate with DataBase.


